      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • accountKey

          HederaKeyPair accountKey
          The HederaKeyPair for the account the key that must sign each transfer out of the account. If receiverSigRequired is true, then it must also sign any transfer into the account.

        • accountNum

          long accountNum
          The account number for the account

        • autoRenewPeriod

          HederaDuration autoRenewPeriod
          the account is charged to extend its expiration date every this many seconds. If it doesn't have enough, it extends as long as possible. If it is empty when it expires, then it is deleted. Defaults to 60 * 60 * 24 * 30 = 30 days (60s * 60m * 24h * 30d)

        • balance

          long balance

        • claims

          java.util.List<HederaClaim> claims
          the list of claims attached to this account as a result of a query

        • cost

          long cost

        • deleted

          boolean deleted

        • expirationTime

          HederaTimeStamp expirationTime
          The expiration time of the account as a result of a query

        • hederaTransactionID

          HederaTransactionID hederaTransactionID
          The HederaTransactionID for a transaction in relation to this account

        • initialBalance

          long initialBalance
          The initial balance when creating a new account

        • keyPairs

          java.util.List<HederaKeyPair> keyPairs

        • logger

          ch.qos.logback.classic.Logger logger

        • maxReceiveProxyFraction

          int maxReceiveProxyFraction
          when another account tries to proxy stake to this account, accept it only if the proxyFraction from that other account is at most maxReceiveProxyFraction

        • newAccountKey

          HederaKeyPair newAccountKey
          The new HederaKeyPair for the account the key that must sign each transfer out of the account. If receiverSigRequired is true, then it must also sign any transfer into the account.

        • newRealmAdminKey

          HederaKeyPair newRealmAdminKey
          The new realm administration key HederaKeyPair for the account note: if a newRealmAdminKeySig is specified, this will be ignored

        • node

          HederaNode node

        • precheckResult

          com.hederahashgraph.api.proto.java.ResponseCodeEnum precheckResult

        • proxyAccountID

          HederaAccountID proxyAccountID
          the HederaAccountID to proxy tokens to If proxyAccountID is null, or is an invalid account, or is an account that isn't a node, then this account is automatically proxy staked to a node chosen by the network, but without earning payments. If the proxyAccountID account refuses to accept proxy staking at the given fraction, or if it is not currently running a node, then it will behave as if both proxyAccountID and proxyFraction were null.

        • proxyFraction

          int proxyFraction
          payments earned from proxy staking are shared between the node and this account, with proxyFraction / 10000 going to this account

        • proxyReceived

          long proxyReceived

        • realmNum

          long realmNum
          The realm number for the account

        • receiveRecordThreshold

          long receiveRecordThreshold
          create an account record for any transaction depositing more than this many tinybars

        • receiverSigRequired

          boolean receiverSigRequired
          if true, this account's key must sign any transaction depositing into this account (in addition to all withdrawals). This field is immutable; it cannot be changed by a CryptoUpdate transaction.

        • records

          java.util.List<HederaTransactionRecord> records

        • sendRecordThreshold

          long sendRecordThreshold
          create an account record for any transaction withdrawing more than this many tinybars

        • shardNum

          long shardNum
          The shard number for the account

        • stakers

        • stateProof

          byte[] stateProof

        • txQueryDefaults

  • Package com.hedera.sdk.contract

    • Class com.hedera.sdk.contract.HederaContract extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • adminKey

          HederaKeyPair adminKey
          The HederaKeyPair representing the contract's administration key initially null the state of the instance and its fields can be modified arbitrarily if this key signs a transaction to modify it. If this is null, then such modifications are not possible, and there is no administrator that can override the normal operation of this smart contract instance. Note that if it is created with no admin keys, then there is no administrator to authorize changing the admin keys, so there can never be any admin keys for that instance.

        • amount

          long amount
          initial number of tinybars to put into the cryptocurrency account associated with and owned by the smart contract

        • autoRenewPeriod

          HederaDuration autoRenewPeriod
          A HederaDuration representing the auto renew period of a smart contract initially null the instance will charge its account every this many seconds to renew for this long

        • byteCode

          byte[] byteCode

        • constructionParameters

          byte[] constructionParameters
          Parameters supplied when creating a smart contract (in the solidity format)

        • contractAccountAccountNum

          long contractAccountAccountNum
          The contract's account number

        • contractAccountRealmNum

          long contractAccountRealmNum
          The contract's account's realm number

        • contractAccountShardNum

          long contractAccountShardNum
          The contract's account's shard number

        • contractNum

          long contractNum
          the smart contract number

        • cost

          long cost

        • expirationTime

          HederaTimeStamp expirationTime
          A HederaTimeStamp containing the expiration time for a smart contract initially null extend the expiration of the instance and its account to this time (no effect if it already is this time or later)

        • fileID

          HederaFileID fileID
          The HederaFileID containing the smart contract's bytecode initially null A copy will be made and held by the contract instance, and have the same expiration time as the instance.

        • functionParameters

        • gas

          the gas to pay to run a smart contract or smart contract function

        • hederaContractFunctionResult

        • logger

          ch.qos.logback.classic.Logger logger

        • maxResultSize

          long maxResultSize
          max number of bytes that the a smart contract call result might include. The run will fail if it would have returned more than this number of bytes.

        • newRealmAdminKey

          HederaKeyPair newRealmAdminKey
          The HederaKeyPair representing the realm's administration key initially null if realmID is null, then this the admin key for the new realm that will be created

        • node

          HederaNode node

        • precheckResult

          com.hederahashgraph.api.proto.java.ResponseCodeEnum precheckResult

        • proxyAccountID

          HederaAccountID proxyAccountID
          ID of the account to which this account is proxy staked. If proxyAccountID is null, or is an invalid account, or is an account that isn't a node, then this account is automatically proxy staked to a node chosen by the network, but without earning payments. If the proxyAccountID account refuses to accept proxy staking at the given fraction, or if it is not currently running a node, then it will behave as if both proxyAccountID and proxyFraction were null. initially null

        • proxyFraction

          int proxyFraction
          payments earned from proxy staking are shared between the node and this instance's account, with proxyFraction / 10000 going to this account

        • realmNum

          long realmNum
          the realm number for the smart contract realm in which to create this (leave this null to create a new realm)

        • shardNum

          long shardNum
          the shard number for the smart contract

        • solidityContractAccountID

          java.lang.String solidityContractAccountID

          byte[] stateProof

        • storage

          long storage

        • transactionRecords
